{"namespace":"dogcat","id":"20pq","title":"Support external .dogcats directory via .dogcatrc config file","description":"Allow users to place their .dogcats folder outside the repo by creating a .dogcatrc file in the repo root (or any parent directory). The file contains a single path pointing to the .dogcats directory. Supports relative and absolute paths. Discovery uses the same upward search pattern: look for .dogcatrc first, read the path from it, then fall back to searching for .dogcats/ directly.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","owner":"post@rykroken.net","parent":null,"labels":[],"external_ref":null,"design":null,"acceptance":null,"notes":null,"created_at":"2026-02-06T07:01:57.865964+01:00","created_by":"post@rykroken.net","updated_at":"2026-02-06T07:01:57.865991+01:00","updated_by":null,"closed_at":null,"closed_by":null,"deleted_at":null,"deleted_by":null,"delete_reason":null,"original_type":null,"comments":[],"duplicate_of":null,"metadata":{}}
